# EMWRAPS Blog Post Pipeline — How to Create & Publish

> The complete guide to going from photos on your computer to a live blog post on emwraps.net.

---

## The Pipeline (Overview)

```
📸 Photos on your computer
     ↓
📤 Upload to CMS Media Library (stored in Supabase S3)
     ↓
📝 Create Blog Post in CMS (title, content, images, SEO)
     ↓
✅ Set status to "Published"
     ↓
🌐 Automatically appears on emwraps.net/blog
```

**That's it.** No code deploys needed. No git pushes. The website reads from the CMS API in real-time.

---

## Method 1: CMS Admin Panel (Recommended)

### Step 1: Open the CMS Admin

| Environment | URL |
|-------------|-----|
| **Production** | [https://cms.emwraps.net/admin](https://cms.emwraps.net/admin) |
| **Local dev** | [http://localhost:3001/admin](http://localhost:3001/admin) |

Login with your admin credentials.

### Step 2: Upload Photos

1. In the sidebar, click **Media**
2. Click **Create New**
3. Drag & drop your photo (or click to browse)
4. Fill in the **Alt Text** — this is important for SEO
   - Good: `Ferrari SF90 XX full body PPF — front three-quarter view`
   - Bad: `IMG_4521`
5. Click **Save**
6. Repeat for each photo you want in the post

> [!TIP]
> **Image recommendations:**
> - Format: JPG or PNG (JPG preferred for photos)
> - Size: At least 1200px wide for hero images
> - The CMS auto-generates resized versions (thumbnail, card, hero sizes)
> - Alt text helps Google Images rank your photos

### Step 3: Create the Blog Post

1. In the sidebar, click **Posts**
2. Click **Create New**
3. Fill in the fields:

#### Required Fields

| Field | What to Enter | Example |
|-------|--------------|---------|
| **Title** | Post headline | `BMW M4 — Satin Black Full Body Wrap` |
| **Slug** | URL-friendly version (auto-generates from title) | `bmw-m4-satin-black-full-body-wrap` |
| **Featured Image** | Select from Media Library — this is the hero/card image | Pick your best shot |
| **Content** | Rich text body (see below) | Write your article |
| **Author** | Select your user | `EMW admin` |
| **Status** | Set to `Published` when ready | `Published` |

#### Recommended Fields

| Field | What to Enter | Example |
|-------|--------------|---------|
| **Excerpt** | 1-2 sentence summary (shows on blog listing cards, max 300 chars) | `A stunning satin black wrap transformation on a BMW M4 Competition...` |
| **Category** | Select from dropdown | `Project Spotlight` |
| **Related Service** | Links post to a service page | `Vinyl Wraps` |
| **Tags** | Add relevant keywords (one per row) | `BMW`, `M4`, `Satin Black`, `Full Wrap` |
| **Published At** | Date to display | Pick today's date |

### Step 4: Write the Content (Rich Text Editor)

The content editor is Lexical-based. Here's how to structure a project spotlight post:

#### Suggested Structure
```
[Opening paragraph — what the project is, why it's cool]

## The Build
[Details about the vehicle, what was done, materials used]

[📸 INSERT IMAGE — click the image icon in toolbar, select from Media]

## Why [Material/Service]?
• Bullet point 1
• Bullet point 2
• Bullet point 3

[📸 INSERT IMAGE]

## The Result
[Final thoughts, outcome description]

[📸 INSERT IMAGE]

## Ready to [Action]?
[Call to action — contact info, phone number]
```

#### How to Insert Inline Images
1. In the rich text editor, place your cursor where you want the image
2. Click the **image/upload icon** in the toolbar (or type `/` to open the slash menu)
3. Select **Upload** from the block menu
4. Choose an image from your Media Library
5. The image will appear inline in the content

### Step 5: SEO Tab

The SEO tab auto-generates from your post data, but you can override:

| Field | Auto-Generated | Override If... |
|-------|---------------|----------------|
| **Meta Title** | `{Title} — EMWRAPS \| Seattle Vehicle Wraps & PPF` | You want a shorter/punchier title |
| **Meta Description** | Uses your Excerpt (max 160 chars) | You want different text for Google |
| **Meta Image** | Uses your Featured Image | You want a different OG card image |

> [!TIP]
> Click **Auto-generate** buttons in the SEO tab to populate these fields from your post data.

### Step 6: Publish

1. At the top of the editor, change `Draft` → click **Publish**
2. Also set the **Status** field to `Published`
3. Click **Save**

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Both are needed:** Payload's built-in draft system (the Publish button at top) AND the custom Status field must both be set to Published. If the post doesn't appear on the website, check both.

### Step 7: Verify

Open your browser and go to:
- **Blog listing:** [https://emwraps.net/blog](https://emwraps.net/blog)
- **Your new post:** `https://emwraps.net/blog/{your-slug}`

The post should appear immediately — no deploy needed.

